main event: An unidentified object was observed near Meade, Kansas on June 25, 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as an 'intermittent fire' and was observed for 2 seconds.
The object appeared west of Meade and disappeared in the north-northwest direction.
The object was estimated to be at an altitude between 20,000 to 40,000 feet.
Weather conditions did not account for the sighting, and no meteorological or other conditions could explain the observation.
No photographs or physical evidence were available.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object described as 'intermittent fire'
